text: Hana Orgoníková (8 December 1946 - 5 June 2014) was a Czech politician. She was an MP for the Czech Social Democratic Party (CSDP) from 1989 until her death. Orgoníková was born in Přibyslav, Czechoslovakia. She was divorced and had two children, Vladimír and Lucie. Orgoníková died after a long illness on 5 June 2014 in Hradec Králové, Czech Republic, aged 67. ==References== ==Other websites== * Hana Orgoníková at Parlament České republiky, Poslanecká sněmovna Category:1946 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Czech politicians Category:Disease-related deaths in the Czech Republic
